result.execSummary:
The defendant Joshua S Hadlock was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant shall not operate a motor vehicle on a highway in this State unless authorized to do so by DMV
Defendant shall not operate a motor vehicle anywhere with any amount of alcohol in his system.
Defendant shall not operate a vehicle anywhere with any detectable amount of restricted controlled substances in blood, unless authorized by healthcare provider.

Defendant to pay supervision fees as determined by DOC.
Defendant shall submit to any assessments and fully participate in any counseling deemed appropriate by the Agent and abide by any treatment recommendations.
Provide biological specimen to State Crime Lab for DNA analysis.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
Defendant shall receive Alcohol and other Drug Assessment from Waupaca County DHHS or other licensed agency as determined by Agent and abide by any treatment recommendations.

Defendant to provide verified documentation to the Agent.
